  "text": "LPS is a principal component of the outer membrane of Gram-negative bacteria and can enter the blood stream and elicit inflammatory responses that may lead to shock and ultimately to death [CITATION_1] . LPS-induced lung injury in the rat is frequently used as a model for studying ALI [CITATION_2] . Thus, this model was used in the present study to investigate the prevention of AAP on LPS-induced ALI in mice.",
